  "text": "Firefox's CSS calc() value handling involves a call chain that processes calc() expressions parsed by Servo and then converts the results with overflow protection:\n\n## Parsing\nThe ServoCSSParser.cpp/h files (layout/style/ServoCSSParser.cpp and layout/style/ServoCSSParser.h) provide the C++ interface to Servo's CSS parser. The actual parsing of calc() expressions occurs in Servo (Rust), which is called through the Servo_ParseProperty function.\n\n## Value Resolution and Overflow Handling\nWhen calc() values are resolved, the process flows through:\n\n1. **ServoStyleConstsInlines.h** contains the StyleCalcLengthPercentage class with two critical methods:\n   - ResolveToCSSPixels(): Calls Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage to resolve the calc expression to a numeric value\n   - Resolve(): Takes the resolved CSS pixel value and converts it to app units (nscoord) using a Rounder function\n\n2. **gfx/src/nsCoord.h** provides overflow-safe conversion functions that prevent crashes from extreme values:\n   - NSToCoordRoundWithClamp (lines 108-128): Bounds-checks floating point values before converting to nscoord to avoid overflow. It clamps values to nscoord_MAX or nscoord_MIN.\n   - NSCoordSaturatingMultiply (lines 155-166): Safely multiplies coordinates with saturation\n   - NSCoordSaturatingAdd (lines 173-182): Safely adds coordinates with saturation  \n   - NSCoordSaturatingSubtract (lines 195-215): Safely subtracts coordinates with saturation\n   - NSFloatPixelsToAppUnits and NSDoublePixelsToAppUnits: Convert pixel values to app units with overflow clamping\n\n3. **nsComputedDOMStyle.cpp/h** contains SetValueToLengthPercentage() which clamps negative calc() values to 0 when reporting computed styles to JavaScript.\n\n4. **nsStyleStruct.cpp/h** handles value resolution for specific properties (margins, padding, sizes) and calls Servo_ResolveAnchorFunctionsInCalcPercentage for anchor-related calc expressions.\n\n5. **ServoStyleConstsForwards.h** provides forward declarations for StyleCalcLengthPercentage and StyleGenericCalcNode types that are generated from Servo.\n\n6. **CSSMathSum.cpp** in typedom represents CSS Typed OM calc() expressions through the CSSMathSum class.\n\nThe critical overflow protection occurs in NSToCoordRoundWithClamp in nsCoord.h, which prevents the crash by checking if values exceed the valid range for nscoord (which is a 32-bit signed integer with range from -(2^30-1) to (2^30-1)) before conversion. This is called from ServoStyleConstsInlines.h during the Resolve template method when converting calc() results from CSS pixels to app units via the rounding function."
}

